Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry all produce.

Place @jasmine rice{3/4%cup} in a #fine-mesh strainer{} and rinse until water runs clear. Peel and mince or grate @ginger{1%thumb}. Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}, separating whites from greens; mince whites. Zest and quarter @lime{1}.

> 4 SERVINGS: Adjust racks to top and middle positions.

Thoroughly shake @coconut milk{5.07%ounce} in container before opening.

In a #small pot{}, combine 1/4 cup coconut milk (you'll use the rest later), @water{1%cup}, @butter{1%tablespoon}, @sugar{1%tsp}, and a big pinch of @salt{}. Bring to a boil, then stir in rice, cover, and reduce heat to low. Cook until liquid has absorbed and rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}. Keep covered off heat for at least ~{10%minutes} or until ready to serve.

> 4 SERVINGS: Use 1/2 cup coconut milk, 1¾ cups water, 2 TBSP butter, and 2 tsp sugar.

While rice cooks, in a #large bowl{}, combine @ground pork{10%ounce}, @panko breadcrumbs{1/4%cup}, ginger, scallion whites, @ponzu sauce{6%milliliters}, @salt{3/4%tsp}, and @pepper{}. Form into 10-12 1 1/2-inch meatballs.

> 4 SERVINGS: Use 1 1/2 tsp kosher salt. Form into 20-24 meatballs.

Place meatballs on one side of a lightly oiled #baking sheet{}. Toss @green beans{6%ounce} on empty side with a drizzle of @vegetable oil{2%teaspoon}, salt, and pepper.

Roast on top rack until meatballs are cooked through and green beans are browned and tender, ~{14-16%minutes}.

> 4 SERVINGS: Divide between 2 sheets; roast meatballs on middle rack and green beans on top rack.

When meatballs and green beans have ~{5%minutes} left, combine @sweet Thai chili sauce{1%ounce} and remaining coconut milk in a #large pan{}; heat over medium-high heat. Bring to a simmer and cook until reduced by about half, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Turn off heat. Stir in a squeeze of lime juice to taste.

Fluff rice with a #fork{} and stir in lime zest. Season with salt and pepper.

Add meatballs to pan with coconut chili sauce; toss to coat.

Divide rice between #bowls{}; top with meatballs and green beans. Spoon any remaining sauce over meatballs. Sprinkle with @peanuts{1/2%ounce} and scallion greens. Serve with remaining lime wedges on the side.